cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper presents a method for adding multiple tasks to a single deep neural network, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on image classification tasks, which suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely sub-category. The method involves pruning and re-training the network, which involves optimization techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper evaluates the method on large-scale datasets, which suggests natural language processing (cs.CL) as a possible sub-category.
